{"batch":"api_surface_coherence","batch_index":18,"assessments":{"api_surface_coherence":66.0},"dimension_notes":{"api_surface_coherence":{"evidence":["The scripts expose several near-equivalent network/data-loading APIs with different shapes: `fetch_status(session, gid, timeout=30)` returns `(status_code, response)` in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py`, `fetch_game_json_with_retry(session, gid, tries=5)` returns a string status plus optional payload in the same file, `fetch_json_with_retry(session, url, timeout=30, tries=4)` in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` returns parsed JSON or raises, and `build_table(game_id)` / `build_def_foul_context(game_id)` in the single-game scripts hide the request entirely and return a DataFrame.","Similar public builders do not share one predictable failure contract. `build_possession_table_for_game(session, game_id)` returns `None` for empty or malformed game data in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py`, `parse_possessions(pbp_df)` raises `ValueError` when team IDs are not exactly two in `step2_build_possessions.py`, `build_table(game_id)` and `build_def_foul_context(game_id)` let `requests` failures propagate, and `process_game(session, gid)` converts failures into `{\"status\": ...}` dictionaries.","API naming and parameter conventions drift across the same workflow: some functions use `gid`, others use `game_id`; some accept a prebuilt `session` while sibling helpers construct their own request; some take raw `actions` or `pbp_df`, while similarly named `build_*` functions fetch remotely from just a game id. A reader cannot infer from one script how the next script wants to be called or what it returns on failure."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"inconsistent_game_fetch_api_shapes","summary":"Game-loading helpers for the same NBA feed use incompatible parameter and return shapes.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py"],"evidence":["`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` splits feed access across `fetch_status(session, gid, timeout=30)` returning `(status_code, response)` and `fetch_game_json_with_retry(session, gid, tries=5)` returning `(\"ok\", payload)` or `(\"missing\", None)`.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` uses `fetch_json_with_retry(session, url, timeout=30, tries=4)` instead, which takes a full URL and either returns parsed JSON or raises an exception.","`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` and `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py` expose `build_table(game_id)` and `build_def_foul_context(game_id)` that perform their own HTTP request internally, so callers cannot reuse the session-based pattern used by the season scripts."],"suggestion":"Introduce one shared game-feed API with one input shape, such as `load_game_actions(session, game_id)`, and one documented result contract. Then make the season and single-game scripts build on that instead of each defining a different fetch wrapper.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"cloned_script_interfaces"},{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"mixed_failure_contracts_across_builders","summary":"Closely related builder functions alternate between raising, returning `None`, and returning status dictionaries.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","step2_build_possessions.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_table_for_game` in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` returns `None` when actions are empty, when game time cannot be computed, or when the team count is not two.","`parse_possessions` in `step2_build_possessions.py` raises `ValueError(\"Expected exactly 2 team IDs in game data.\")` for the same kind of malformed input instead of returning `None`.","`process_game` in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` wraps failures into dictionaries like `{\"status\": \"missing\"}` or `{\"status\": \"error\"}`, while `build_table` and `build_def_foul_context` let `requests.get(...).raise_for_status()` exceptions escape directly."],"suggestion":"Pick one public error contract for this pipeline, for example typed exceptions or a single result object with `status`, `data`, and `error`, and apply it to all builder/fetch functions so callers can handle failures the same way everywhere.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"cloned_script_interfaces"},{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"similar_build_functions_hide_different_inputs","summary":"Functions with similar names expect different levels of preprocessed input, so names do not predict usage.","related_files":["step2_build_possessions.py","calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"],"evidence":["`parse_possessions(pbp_df)` in `step2_build_possessions.py` expects a play-by-play DataFrame that already has `game_seconds_elapsed` prepared by the caller.","`calculate_wmi_rawgame(df)` in `calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py` expects a possession-model table with `L_t`, `F_t`, and `N_t` already present.","Nearby helpers with similarly top-level roles, such as `build_foul_vector(actions)` and `build_possession_table_for_game(session, game_id)`, instead start from raw action arrays or just a game id and do their own preprocessing. The module-level API does not clearly separate raw-input functions from already-normalized-table functions."],"suggestion":"Make the boundary explicit in names and module structure, such as `load_game_actions`, `build_possession_features_from_actions`, and `calculate_wmi_from_possession_table`, so callers can tell whether a function expects raw feed data, normalized events, or final feature tables.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"cloned_script_interfaces"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The project appears to have grown by copying standalone analysis scripts and adapting them locally instead of extracting one stable shared API for feed loading, preprocessing, and WMI calculation.","Because each script owns its own fetch and failure handling, interface decisions drifted independently across single-game and season workflows."],"likely_symptoms":["inconsistent_game_fetch_api_shapes","mixed_failure_contracts_across_builders","similar_build_functions_hide_different_inputs"],"possible_false_positives":["These files are script-oriented rather than imported as a library, so some interface roughness may matter less than it would in a reusable package."]}}
